RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 16600. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGICAL SURPRISE took the lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was hand ridden past the seven sixteenths pole, drew off under steady pressure at the rail on the far turn then kept alert through the stretch. CALLISTO'S BRIGADE rated close to the early pace inside, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced off the rail on the far turn, but flattened later yards while settling for second best. COLONIAL ROAD raced in the five path the first turn and left the turn outside, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and just lasted for third. IRISH FLIGHT settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and passed rivals in the lane. CHARTERED COURSE saved ground on the opening turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but showed little response. TRAP HOLLER became a bit anxious in the gate then stalked two deep, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened. VIESTE showed little response after a half mile. LUNAR GHOST was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Callisto's Brigade
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,bid 3/8,off rail far turn,flattened late,settled 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Magical Surprise
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,hand urged 7/16,drew off far turn,kept alert

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GABARRA was hustled clear then taken in hand, came under pressure past the five sixteenths pole, widened at the rail on the turn then kept alert in the lane. HAMMER gave chase through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn and settled for second best. WISCO DISCO gave chase inside, rounded the turn at the rail, drifted leaving the turn and just got up for third. CALCULATED LUV chased through the backstretch, raced at the rail on the turn then flattened toward mid-stretch. RAINBOW DAY gave chase, rounded the turn off the rail and showed little in the stretch. REV PARKER chased, raced near the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. SUPER BUSTER hesitated at the break and raced well back. TECH DUINN gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path then weakened. ROBCO BOY gave chase, entered the turn off the rail but bore out approaching the head of the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Gabarra
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled clear,rated pace,pressured 5/16,rail turn,kept alert lane

ENTRY.NAME: Robco Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail into turn,bore out near 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 12700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 20, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Wh ere Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCAPTURED RUBY took an immediate lead and rated the pace, inside, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced near the rail on the far turn, drifted leaving the turn but dug in when straightened away and drew away later yards. GOLD TIME VIXEN stalked two deep then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn, drifted nearing the head of the lane, angled in from the heels of Uncaptured Ruby past the eighth pole and dueled to a clear second later yards. PUPPYMONKEYBABY rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened mid-stretch. PRACTICALLY THERE came away a step slow and veered out leaving the gate, settled well back from contention in the three and four paths the first turn, rounded the far turn at the rail and finished evenly to improve her position. STYLISH PAINT raced off the rail the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail, was carried out leaving the turn and weakened in the lane. FLAT DISCOUNT rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in range of the lead in the three path on the far turn, was carried out toward the head of the lane, angled in past the eighth pole but weakened the final sixteenth. SOCIAL EXCLUSION stalked from the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Uncaptured Ruby
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 7/16,rail turn,drifted lane,drew away

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,chased 3/8,3p far turn,carried out 1/8,weaken

ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,carried out 1/8,weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow,veered out break,3& 4p,rail far turn,improved

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREE DROP BACH pressured the pace through the backstretch and raced close two deep on the turn, was carried out leaving the turn but dug in under steady encouragement to take over in later yards and raced clear toward the wire. ADIOS COOL ARROWS had a brief early lead then pressured the pace, raced close at the rail on the turn, dug in to recover the lead toward mid-stretch but relented in the final yards. CAJUN JOE was hustled along the rail and took the lead nearing the three eighths pole, contested the edge at the rail on the turn, drifted leaving the turn and relented in the stretch duel, but held on for third. BRADLEY DO RIGHT chased outside, raced in the five and six paths on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. SISYPHUS gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. SILVER REDESDALE steadied on the chute and gave chase to no avail. GOLD DILEMMA gave chase and raced at the rail on the turn. HOT ROD LOVE appeared off stride and was eased.

ENTRY.NAME: Cajun Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled up inside,edge rail turn,drifted 1/8,held on 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Free Drop Bach
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,close 2d turn,carried out 1/8,up late,clear wire

ENTRY.NAME: Adios Cool Arrows
ENTRY.COMMENT: brief early lead,pressed pace,rail turn,relented later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 13700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE APRIL 20, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since April 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 , if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SISTER'S DUTY gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn, dug in for the lead later yards and ran clear toward the wire. WILLOW MOON pressured the pace inside and took the lead passing the five sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling but was caught flattening stride later yards. GRANDIOSELY chased, raced in the four path on the turn and held onto the nod for third. ULTIMATE BREEZE gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn, dug in leaving the turn, finished well and just missed the nod for third. ALWAYS SOMETHING veered out leaving the gate then closed to the lead toward the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, was met past the five sixteenths, continued close in the three path on the turn but weakened inside the eighth pole. INCLUDE THE BEAST gave close early chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn then flattened the final sixteenth. AT THE HALF was forced out at the break, dropped well back from early contention and raced near the rail on the turn. THUNDER PUNCH gave chase and rounded the turn in the four and five paths. KOBE'S GIRL was not a factor and rounded the turn about the five path.

ENTRY.NAME: Willow Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,up past 5/16,rail turn,caught flattening late

ENTRY.NAME: Include the Beast
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Cefalu John

ENTRY.NAME: Sister's Duty
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,4p turn,dug in lane,up later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Always Something
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered out break,up 7/16,met past 5/16,3p turn,weakened lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KARMA BUS closed to the lead leaving the three eighths pole and set a pressured pace, contested the edge at the rail on the turn and dug in under steady handling to hold on well. MY BALBOA chased through the backstretch, raced close in the three path on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. DIMELO PAPI chased, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. TEMP ME NOT exchanged contact with Golden Asset leaving the gate then chased outside, raced in the five path on the turn and flattened from mid-stretch. DON'T GET CAUGHTUP chased outside, raced in the six path on the turn and passed rivals in the lane. GOLDEN ASSET exchanged contact with Temp Me Not leaving the gate, gave chase and rounded the turn in the three and four paths. GAMBLING FEVER set a pressured early pace but was met and dueled from the three eighths pole, dropped back off the rail midway on the turn and weakened in the stretch. ARYA CHARMING gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. SHINEY GHOST saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Karma Bus
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: up past 3/8,set pressured pace,edge rail turn,held well driving

ENTRY.NAME: Gambling Fever
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Starter Allowance Purse 18600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE OCTOBER 20, 2021. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 20 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 20 Allowed 4 lbs. (Race s Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADVANCE CASH chased through the backstretch and closed to the lead at the rail nearing the top of the lane, dug in under steady handling and held on. ELLE'SBIGSEACRET gave chase, closed to near even terms three wide approaching the eighth pole then dueled through the stretch for second. GOLDEN G gave chase through the backstretch, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. MONTAUK DADDY raced off the pace outside, raced in the six path on the turn and passed rivals in the lane. MR TINGLES took the lead leaving the chute and rated the early pace, came under pressure past the three eighths pole, was met in the three path approaching the head of the lane and weakened. HE IS BONAFIDE gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. COWBOY AT HEART gave chase and rounded the turn about the four path. BIG DADDY D R broke a step slow and awkwardly, never factored and rounded the turn in the six and seven paths. HEY CONGRATS gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 10800. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I SEE NOTHING stalked off the rail on the first turn, gave chase past the half mile pole and steadily improved in the three path on the far turn, dug in determinedly leaving the turn and took the nod in the final strides. SMOKIN SMITTY took over and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and contested the edge at the rail on the far turn, dug in gamely under steady handling leaving the turn but ceded the nod in the final strides. TAKE AIM hesitated leaving the gate then saved ground racing well back, bid past the three eighths pole, steadily improved near the rail on the far turn, angled in toward mid-stretch and finished well for third. HAY DIDDLE DIDDLE raced off the rail the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. FLOOR IT rounded the first turn about the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the six path on the far turn then flattened stride. AGAIN WE MEET saved ground off the pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened stride. CAPT COMPLICATED rounded the first turn in the five path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little in the lane. ROLL ME OVER stalked three wide on the first turn, challenged two deep toward the three eighths pole, but dropped back approaching the quarter, rounded the far turn in the three path and weakened. KING JOEY raced four wide on the opening turn then stalked into the backstretch, gave chase from the three eighths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Hay Diddle Diddle
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

ENTRY.NAME: Take Aim
ENTRY.OWNER: Jones Jr Michael E and JKX Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Smokin Smitty
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 3/8,edge rail turn,game,missed nod

ENTRY.NAME: I See Nothing
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased past 1/2,3p far turn,long duel,nod late
